commit.message:
Run windowmap commands with --sync flag

This will ensure that tdrop waits until the window is mapped before activating
it.  Otherwise tdrop can incorrectly focus another desktop.

Fixes issue #369

verification.payload:
tree 74cb7c5560edd160d270337fd390215d55fab86d

Run windowmap commands with --sync flag

This will ensure that tdrop waits until the window is mapped before activating
it.  Otherwise tdrop can incorrectly focus another desktop.

commit.message:
Improve class handling

- Correctly handle class names with spaces (like "Youtube Music")
- Firefox has the exception of "firefox" being a class name not instance name
  even though it is lowercase (unfortunately since we are guessing class names
  by default we have to add another manual exception list)

Fixes #361.

Validate tdrop windows by setting/checking TDROP_NAME prop

window that has been assigned the window id of a previously closed tdrop

commit.message:
Fix separate dropdowns sometimes grabbing each other

If the wid of a newly created window matches a previously stored wid (i.e. a
previous dropdown or window that has been closed), clear all stored information for it.

Fixes #63.
